# SaveT Site Structure (Next.js)

## Subpage routing

| Page | File | URL |
|------|------|-----|
| Main | `app/savet/page.tsx` | `/savet/` |
| Roadmap | `app/savet/roadmap/page.tsx` | `/savet/roadmap/` |
| Privacy | `app/savet/legal/privacy/page.tsx` | `/savet/legal/privacy/` |
| Terms | `app/savet/legal/terms/page.tsx` | `/savet/legal/terms/` |

Legal URLs are app-accessible — do not change paths.

When adding a new SaveT subpage, also update `app/sitemap.ts` (if public).

## Roadmap page

- **Visibility:** controlled by `showRoadmap` in `lib/config/site.ts` (default `false`)
- **When hidden:** no nav/footer link, `noIndex` metadata, excluded from sitemap; page still builds for agent reference
- **To publish:** set `showRoadmap: true`, add sitemap entry, optional nav link
- **Content:** Canva embed URLs in `lib/content/savet.ts` (`roadmapContent`)
- **Embed ratio:** portrait `aspect-ratio: 100 / 141.4286`

## Navigation

Roadmap is not in main nav unless `showRoadmap` is true and explicitly added to `lib/content/navigation.ts`.

## Legacy redirects

`/features/*` → `/savet/` via Cloudflare 301 (primary) + `public/features/*/index.html` fallback (`scripts/generate-legacy-redirects.mjs`).
